K, Cr, Mn, Fe, Co, Ni, and Cu). We compute physical conditions from a large\nnumber of diagnostics. Thanks to the high ionization of NGC 3918 we detect a\nlarge number of recombination lines of multiple ionization stages of C, N, O\nand Ne. The abundances obtained for these elements by using recently-determined\nstate-of-the-art ICF schemes or simply adding ionic abundances are in very good\nagreement, demonstrating the quality of the recent ICF scheme for high\nionization planetary nebulae.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 23 Jun 2015 16:30:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-08-06"}
