{"id":"1506.07381","submitter":"Jacek Herbrych","authors":"J. Herbrych, A. G. Chazirakis, N. Christakis, J. J. P. Veerman","title":"Dynamics of locally coupled agents with next nearest neighbor\n  interaction","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Differ. Equ. & Dyn. Syst. 29, 487 (2021)","doi":"10.1007/s12591-017-0377-3","report-no":null,"categories":"math.DS","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We consider large but finite systems of identical agents on the line with up\nto next nearest neighbor asymmetric coupling. Each agent is modelled by a\nlinear second order differential equation, linearly coupled to up to four of\nits neighbors. The only restriction we impose is that the equations are\ndecentralized. In this generality we give the conditions for stability of these\nsystems. For stable systems, we find the response to a change of course by the\nleader. This response is at least linear in the size of the flock. Depending on\nthe system parameters, two types of solutions have been found: damped\noscillations and reflectionless waves. The latter is a novel result and a\nfeature of systems with at least next nearest neighbor interactions. Analytical\npredictions are tested in numerical simulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Jun 2015 14:33:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 6 Sep 2016 07:08:19 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 14 Jan 2017 00:50:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-23"}
